# Phase 2.5 — block-by-default + explicit allowlist.
#
# HA writes a large set of runtime files into /config (the bind-mount target
# for ops/ha/). Some of those files contain auth tokens (.storage/auth) or
# PII (shopping_list.json), and HA's `backup` integration writes tarballs of
# the entire /config tree to backups/.  An allowlist-by-extension strategy is
# fragile against future HA file additions.  This file blocks everything by
# default and explicitly tracks only the 4 files we author.
#
# Per security-engineer review on PR #50.
*

# Files we author (tracked):
!.gitignore
!docker-compose.yml
!configuration.yaml
!automations.yaml
